### Bibliographic Note

These endnotes reveal Ferguson's **methodological toolkit**:
- Evolutionary economics: Veblen, Schumpeter, Nelson/Winter,
  Lo's adaptive markets hypothesis, Dawkins
- Behavioral finance: Kahneman/Tversky, Shleifer,
  Thaler/Sunstein
- Crisis theory: Taleb (fat tails), Knight (uncertainty),
  Keynes (animal spirits), Soros (reflexivity)
- LTCM: Perold (HBS cases) as definitive source;
  Dunbar + Lowenstein as narrative accounts
- Globalization critics: Stiglitz, Krugman, Perkins —
  acknowledged but implicitly countered
- **"Chimerica"**: Ferguson's own coinage, introduced
  in his 2007 paper with Schularick

